# Modern Next.js Guidelines (2025)

## core
- use modern, best and latest practices

## TypeScript
- use TypeScript with strict mode
- indent with 4 spaces
- Type props, API responses, and state
- use arrow functions
- dont add the ";" when not necessary

## Components
- Keep components small and focused

## Data Fetching
- Use Suspense for loading states

## Security
- Sanitize inputs
- CSP headers

## the way you should respond
- short, straightforward, highly structured using bullet points and/or tables
- relevant words only
- adopt a sceptical and critical approach